{"title_page": "Marambaia Formation", "text_new": "{{Infobox rockunit\n| name           = Marambaia Formation\n| period         = Cenozoic\n| age            = [[Paleocene]]-[[Pliocene]]<br />~{{fossil range|65|2.6}}\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| caption        = \n| type           = [[Geological formation]]\n| prilithology   = [[Shale]], [[marl]]\n| otherlithology = [[Sandstone]]\n| unitof         = [[Santos Basin#V - Itamambuca Group (Cenozoic, upper post-salt sequence)|Itamambuca Group]]\n| subunits       = \n| underlies      = [[Sepetiba Formation]]\n| overlies       = [[Itaja\u00ed-A\u00e7u Formation|Itaja\u00ed-A\u00e7u Fm.]], [[Jur\u00e9ia Formation|Jur\u00e9ia Fm.]]\n| thickness      = up to {{convert|2700|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| area           = \n| map            = Santos basin map.png\n| map_caption    = Location of the Santos Basin\n| location\n| coordinates    = {{coord|26|6|S|43|43|W|display=inline,title}} \n| region         = [[Santos Basin]], [[Atlantic Ocean#South Atlantic|South Atlantic]]\n| country        = {{BRA}}\n| extent         = <!--{{convert||mi|km}}-->\n| namedfor       = [[Restinga da Marambaia]]\n| namedby        = \n| year_ts        = \n| location_ts    = \n| coordinates_ts = \n| paleocoordinates_ts = \n| region_ts      = \n| country_ts     = \n| thickness_ts   = \n}}\nThe '''Marambaia Formation''' ({{lang-pt|Formac\u00e3o Marambaia}}) is a [[formation (geology)|geological formation]] of the [[Santos Basin]] offshore of the [[Brazil]]ian states of [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]] and [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]]. The predominantly [[shale]] and [[marl]] formation dates to the [[Tertiary]] period and has a maximum thickness of {{convert|2700|m|ft}}. The formation is a [[seal rock|seal]] and [[petroleum reservoir|reservoir rock]] of the Atlanta and Oliva Fields in the Santos Basin.\n\n== Etymology ==\nThe formation is named after [[Restinga da Marambaia]], Rio de Janeiro.\n\n== Description ==\nThe Marambaia Formation is between {{convert|261|and|2000|m|ft}} thick,<ref name=Kiang2008_p32>Kiang Chang et al., 2008, p.32</ref> and consists of grey [[shale]]s and light grey [[marl]]s interbedded with fine-grained [[turbidite|turbiditic]] sandstones. The Marambaia Formation is the deeper lateral equivalent of the [[Iguape Formation]]. This formation in places can be found cropping out at sea bottom. The [[depositional environment]] is thought to be talus and [[open marine]] basin. Biostratigraphic data indicate a Tertiary age.<ref name=Clemente2013_p24>Clemente, 2013, p.24</ref>\n\nThe formation is a [[seal rock|seal]],<ref name=Contreras2011_p77>Contreras, 2011, p.77</ref> and [[petroleum reservoir|reservoir rock]] in the Atlanta and Oliva Fields of the Santos Basin.<ref name=Vieira2007_p10>Vieira, 2007, p.10</ref><ref name=KaroonList>{{Cite web |url=http://www.karoon.com.br/en/index.php/proyecto-brasil/?img=6&id=38 |title=Santos Basin Fields |access-date=2017-09-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907123836/http://www.karoon.com.br/en/index.php/proyecto-brasil/?img=6&id=38 |archive-date=2017-09-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Brazil|Geology}}\n* [[Campos Basin]]\n\n{{clearboth}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite LSA |last=Clemente |first=Pilar |year=2013 |title=Petroleum geology of the Campos and Santos basins, Lower Cretaceous Brazilian sector of the South Atlantic margin |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Pilar_Clemente/publication/236972647_Petroleum_geology_of_the_Campos_and_Santos_basins_Lower_Cretaceous_Brazilian_sector_of_the_South_Atlantic_margin/links/0deec51a8c68082bc8000000.pdf |publisher=[[Technical University of Denmark|Danmarks Tekniske Universitet]] |pages=1\u201333 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Contreras |first=Jorham |year=2011 |title=Seismo-stratigraphy and numerical basin modeling of the southern Brazilian continental margin (Campos, Santos, and Pelotas basins) (PhD thesis) |url=http://archiv.ub.uni-heidelberg.de/volltextserver/12323/1/Promotion_JContreras.pdf |publisher=[[Heidelberg University|Ruprecht-Karls-Universit\u00e4t Heidelberg]] |pages=1\u2013171 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Kiang Chang |first=Hung |last2=Assine |first2=Mario Luis |last3=Santos Corr\u00eaa |first3=Fernando |last4=Setsuo Tinen |first4=Julio |last5=Campane Vidal |first5=Alexandre |last6=Koike |first6=Luzia |year=2008 |title=Sistemas petrol\u00edferos e modelos de acumula\u00e7\u00e3o de hidrocarbonetos na Bacia de Santos |url=http://geomuseu.ist.utl.pt/GSP2012/GSP2009/Casos%20de%20estudo%20SP/GSP%20Bacia%20Santos.pdf |journal=[[Brazilian Journal of Geology|Revista Brasileira de Geoci\u00eancias]] |volume=38 |pages=29\u201346 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Vieira |first=Juliana |year=2007 |title=Brazil Round 9 - Santos Basin |url=http://www.brasil-rounds.gov.br/round9/arquivos_r9/palestras/Santos(ingles).pdf |publisher=[[Ag\u00eancia Nacional do Petr\u00f3leo|ANP]] |pages=1\u201373 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n\n[[Category:Geologic formations of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Santos Basin]]\n[[Category:Neogene Brazil]]\n[[Category:Paleogene Brazil]]\n[[Category:Neogene System of South America]]\n[[Category:Paleogene System of South America]]\n[[Category:Shale formations]]\n[[Category:Marl formations]]\n[[Category:Sandstone formations]]\n[[Category:Deep marine deposits]]\n[[Category:Turbidite deposits]]\n[[Category:Reservoir rock formations]]\n[[Category:Petroleum in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Geography of Paran\u00e1 (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of Rio de Janeiro (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of Santa Catarina (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Tupi\u2013Guarani languages]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox rockunit\n| name           = Marambaia Formation\n| period         = Cenozoic\n| age            = [[Paleocene]]-[[Pliocene]]<br />~{{fossil range|65|2.6}}\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| caption        = \n| type           = [[Geological formation]]\n| prilithology   = [[Shale]], [[marl]]\n| otherlithology = [[Sandstone]]\n| unitof         = [[Santos Basin#V - Itamambuca Group (Cenozoic, upper post-salt sequence)|Itamambuca Group]]\n| subunits       = \n| underlies      = [[Sepetiba Formation]]\n| overlies       = [[Itaja\u00ed-A\u00e7u Formation|Itaja\u00ed-A\u00e7u Fm.]], [[Jur\u00e9ia Formation|Jur\u00e9ia Fm.]]\n| thickness      = up to {{convert|2700|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| area           = \n| map            = Santos basin map.png\n| map_caption    = Location of the Santos Basin\n| location\n| coordinates    = {{coord|26|6|S|43|43|W|display=inline,title}} \n| region         = [[Santos Basin]], [[Atlantic Ocean#South Atlantic|South Atlantic]]\n| country        = {{BRA}}\n| extent         = <!--{{convert||mi|km}}-->\n| namedfor       = [[Restinga da Marambaia]]\n| namedby        = \n| year_ts        = \n| location_ts    = \n| coordinates_ts = \n| paleocoordinates_ts = \n| region_ts      = \n| country_ts     = \n| thickness_ts   = \n}}\nThe '''Marambaia Formation''' ({{lang-pt|Formac\u00e3o Marambaia}}) is a [[formation (geology)|geological formation]] of the [[Santos Basin]] offshore of the [[Brazil]]ian states of [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Paran\u00e1 (state)|Paran\u00e1]] and [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]]. The predominantly [[shale]] and [[marl]] formation dates to the [[Tertiary]] period and has a maximum thickness of {{convert|2700|m|ft}}. The formation is a [[seal rock|seal]] and [[petroleum reservoir|reservoir rock]] of the Atlanta and Oliva Fields in the Santos Basin.\n\n== Etymology ==\nThe formation is named after [[Restinga da Marambaia]], Rio de Janeiro.\n\n== Description ==\nThe Marambaia Formation is between {{convert|261|and|2000|m|ft}} thick,<ref name=Kiang2008_p32>Kiang Chang et al., 2008, p.32</ref> and consists of grey [[shale]]s and light grey [[marl]]s interbedded with fine-grained [[turbidite|turbiditic]] sandstones. The Marambaia Formation is the deeper lateral equivalent of the [[Iguape Formation]]. This formation in places can be found cropping out at sea bottom. The [[depositional environment]] is thought to be talus and [[open marine]] basin. Biostratigraphic data indicate a Tertiary age.<ref name=Clemente2013_p24>Clemente, 2013, p.24</ref>\n\nThe formation is a [[seal rock|seal]],<ref name=Contreras2011_p77>Contreras, 2011, p.77</ref> and [[petroleum reservoir|reservoir rock]] in the Atlanta and Oliva Fields of the Santos Basin.<ref name=Vieira2007_p10>Vieira, 2007, p.10</ref><ref name=KaroonList>{{Cite web |url=http://www.karoon.com.br/en/index.php/proyecto-brasil/?img=6&id=38 |title=Santos Basin Fields |access-date=2017-09-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907123836/http://www.karoon.com.br/en/index.php/proyecto-brasil/?img=6&id=38 |archive-date=2017-09-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Brazil|Geology}}\n* [[Campos Basin]]\n\n{{clearboth}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite LSA |last=Clemente |first=Pilar |year=2013 |title=Petroleum geology of the Campos and Santos basins, Lower Cretaceous Brazilian sector of the South Atlantic margin |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Pilar_Clemente/publication/236972647_Petroleum_geology_of_the_Campos_and_Santos_basins_Lower_Cretaceous_Brazilian_sector_of_the_South_Atlantic_margin/links/0deec51a8c68082bc8000000.pdf |publisher=[[Technical University of Denmark|Danmarks Tekniske Universitet]] |pages=1\u201333 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Contreras |first=Jorham |year=2011 |title=Seismo-stratigraphy and numerical basin modeling of the southern Brazilian continental margin (Campos, Santos, and Pelotas basins) (PhD thesis) |url=http://archiv.ub.uni-heidelberg.de/volltextserver/12323/1/Promotion_JContreras.pdf |publisher=[[Heidelberg University|Ruprecht-Karls-Universit\u00e4t Heidelberg]] |pages=1\u2013171 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Kiang Chang |first=Hung |last2=Assine |first2=Mario Luis |last3=Santos Corr\u00eaa |first3=Fernando |last4=Setsuo Tinen |first4=Julio |last5=Campane Vidal |first5=Alexandre |last6=Koike |first6=Luzia |year=2008 |title=Sistemas petrol\u00edferos e modelos de acumula\u00e7\u00e3o de hidrocarbonetos na Bacia de Santos |url=http://geomuseu.ist.utl.pt/GSP2012/GSP2009/Casos%20de%20estudo%20SP/GSP%20Bacia%20Santos.pdf |journal=[[Brazilian Journal of Geology|Revista Brasileira de Geoci\u00eancias]] |volume=38 |pages=29\u201346 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Vieira |first=Juliana |year=2007 |title=Brazil Round 9 - Santos Basin |url=http://www.brasil-rounds.gov.br/round9/arquivos_r9/palestras/Santos(ingles).pdf |publisher=[[Ag\u00eancia Nacional do Petr\u00f3leo|ANP]] |pages=1\u201373 |accessdate=2017-09-04}}\n\n[[Category:Geologic formations of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Santos Basin|Formations]]\n[[Category:Neogene Brazil]]\n[[Category:Paleogene Brazil]]\n[[Category:Neogene System of South America]]\n[[Category:Paleogene System of South America]]\n[[Category:Shale formations]]\n[[Category:Marl formations]]\n[[Category:Sandstone formations]]\n[[Category:Deep marine deposits]]\n[[Category:Turbidite deposits]]\n[[Category:Reservoir rock formations]]\n[[Category:Petroleum in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Geography of Paran\u00e1 (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of Rio de Janeiro (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of Santa Catarina (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|Formations]]\n[[Category:Tupi\u2013Guarani languages]]\n", "name_user": "Beagel", "label": "safe", "comment": "cleanup", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marambaia_Formation"}
{"title_page": "Henry Meredith Parker", "text_new": "[[File:H M Parker poet.jpg|thumb|Portrait sketch by [[Colesworthey Grant]]]]\n'''Henry Meredith Parker''' (1796\u20131868) was a [[Great Britain|British]] writer who lived in Calcutta, India, working in the [[Indian Civil Service (British India)|Bengal Civil Service]], who wrote poems and essays. He contributed a lot to local Indian periodicals such as the ''Calcutta Review''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/poetsofjohncompa00dunn#page/66/|title=Poets of John Company|author=Dunn, Theodore Douglas|publisher=Thacker, Spink & Co.|year=1921|place=Calcutta|pages=66\u201377}}</ref> A major work was his two volume Bole Ponjis (\"''Punch Bowl''\"). Along with Theodore Dickens, Ashutosh Dey and others he established the Union Bank of Calcutta in 1829.\n\nParker's mother was a famous Covent Garden Theatre dancer and in his youth he played violin at the playhouse. He started work for Lord Moira at the Tower of London followed by a clerkship in the Commissariat. He served in the Peninsular War and joined the Bengal Civil Service in 1813 as a writer. He worked as an assistant to the Superintendent of the Western Salt Chaukis, as an assistant Salt Agent in Chittagong and then in the Customs department. He retired in 1842 with an entertaining farewell performance that he gave at the Sans Souci Theatre in Park Street. In his spare time he wrote [[Farce|farcical plays]] for the Calcutta theatre, many drawn from French sources. He supported [[James Silk Buckingham]] and the publication of his ''Calcutta Journal''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/bygonedaysinindi00dewauoft#page/n257/mode/1up|title=Bygone days in India|author=Dewar, Douglas|publisher=John Lane The Bodley Head Ltd.|year=1922|place=London|page=188}}</ref> He was known for supporting cultural integration between Indians and Europeans. [[Henry Louis Vivian Derozio]] wrote a ''Sonnet to Henry Meredith Parker''.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Fakeer of Jungheera, a Metrical Tale: And Other Poems|author=Derozio, Henry Louis Vivian Derozio| publisher=Samuel Smith|year= 1828}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.150222/2015.150222.Complete-Works-Of-Henry-Louis-Vivian-Derozio#page/n267/|title=Song of the storym petrel. Complete works of Henry Louis Vivian Derozio|year=2001|page=201}}</ref> [[Kashiprasad Ghosh|Kasiprasad Ghosh]] wrote a poem to Parker.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.175369/2015.175369.The-Shair-And-Other-Poems#page/n59/|title=The Shair And Other Poems|author=Ghosh, Kasiprasad|year=1830|pages=53\u201354}}</ref>\n\nIn his ''Indian War Song'' published in 1824 he foresaw the 1857 rebellion. This was written under the initials \"C.J.\" but he also wrote under other pseudonyms including '''Bernard Wycliffe'''.<ref>[C.J.] (1824) ''Oriental Herald'' '''2''':62</ref>\n<poem>\nLet the Musulman rise, with his old battle cry, \nFor the glad hour of freedom and vengeance is nigh; \nLet him think on the sceptre his forefathers swayed, \nAnd the might of past ages shall rest on his blade.\n\nWill the fiery rajpoot hear the trumpet that rings \nWith a nation's appeal to the offspring of kings, \nNor rush to the field, like his proud sires of old, \nThe vanguard of valour, and guide of the bold?\n\nSound! sound to horse! hark! the loud clanging hoof \nAnd the neigh of impatience gives gallant reproof; \nMarch! and the trump of our Durrahs shall roll, \nLike a fast-moving storm on the infidel's soul.\n</poem>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikisource author}}\n* [https://archive.org/details/boleponjisconta01parkgoog Bole Ponjis. Volume I]\n* [https://archive.org/details/boleponjisconta00parkgoog Bole Ponjis. Volume II]\n\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Parker, Henry Meredith}}\n[[Category:1796 births]]\n[[Category:1868 deaths]]\n[[Category:British male writers]]\n[[Category:Indian Civil Service (British India) officers]]\n\n\n{{UK-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:H M Parker poet.jpg|thumb|Portrait sketch by [[Colesworthey Grant]]]]\n'''Henry Meredith Parker''' (1796\u20131868) was a [[Great Britain|British]] writer who lived in Calcutta, India, working in the [[Indian Civil Service (British India)|Bengal Civil Service]], who wrote poems and essays. He contributed a lot to local Indian periodicals such as the ''Calcutta Review''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/poetsofjohncompa00dunn#page/66/|title=Poets of John Company|author=Dunn, Theodore Douglas|publisher=Thacker, Spink & Co.|year=1921|place=Calcutta|pages=66-77}}</ref> A major work was his two volume Bole Ponjis (\"''Punch Bowl''\"). Along with Theodore Dickens, Ashutosh Dey and others he established the Union Bank of Calcutta in 1829.\n\nParker's mother was a famous Covent Garden Theatre dancer and in his youth he played violin at the playhouse. He started work for Lord Moira at the Tower of London followed by a clerkship in the Commissariat. He served in the Peninsular War and joined the Bengal Civil Service in 1813 as a writer. He worked as an assistant to the Superintendent of the Western Salt Chaukis, as an assistant Salt Agent in Chittagong and then in the Customs department. He retired in 1842 with an entertaining farewell performance that he gave at the Sans Souci Theatre in Park Street. In his spare time he wrote [[Farce|farcical plays]] for the Calcutta theatre, many drawn from French sources. He supported [[James Silk Buckingham]] and the publication of his ''Calcutta Journal''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/bygonedaysinindi00dewauoft#page/n257/mode/1up|title=Bygone days in India|author=Dewar, Douglas|publisher=John Lane The Bodley Head Ltd.|year=1922|place=London|page=188}}</ref> He was known for supporting cultural integration between Indians and Europeans. [[Henry Louis Vivian Derozio]] wrote a ''Sonnet to Henry Meredith Parker''.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Fakeer of Jungheera, a Metrical Tale: And Other Poems|author=Derozio, Henry Louis Vivian Derozio| publisher=Samuel Smith|year= 1828}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.150222/2015.150222.Complete-Works-Of-Henry-Louis-Vivian-Derozio#page/n267/|title=Song of the storym petrel. Complete works of Henry Louis Vivian Derozio|year=2001|page=201}}</ref> [[Kashiprasad Ghosh|Kasiprasad Ghosh]] wrote a poem to Parker.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.175369/2015.175369.The-Shair-And-Other-Poems#page/n59/|title=The Shair And Other Poems|author=Ghosh, Kasiprasad|year=1830|pages=53-54}}</ref>\n\nIn his ''Indian War Song'' published in 1824 he foresaw the 1857 rebellion. This was written under the initials \"C.J.\" but he also wrote under other pseudonyms including '''Bernard Wycliffe'''.<ref>[C.J.] (1824) ''Oriental Herald'' '''2''':62</ref>\n<poem>\nLet the Musulman rise, with his old battle cry, \nFor the glad hour of freedom and vengeance is nigh; \nLet him think on the sceptre his forefathers swayed, \nAnd the might of past ages shall rest on his blade.\n\nWill the fiery rajpoot hear the trumpet that rings \nWith a nation's appeal to the offspring of kings, \nNor rush to the field, like his proud sires of old, \nThe vanguard of valour, and guide of the bold?\n\nSound! sound to horse! hark! the loud clanging hoof \nAnd the neigh of impatience gives gallant reproof; \nMarch! and the trump of our Durrahs shall roll, \nLike a fast-moving storm on the infidel's soul.\n</poem>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikisource author}}\n* [https://archive.org/details/boleponjisconta01parkgoog Bole Ponjis. Volume I]\n* [https://archive.org/details/boleponjisconta00parkgoog Bole Ponjis. Volume II]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Parker, Henry Meredith}}\n[[Category:1796 births]]\n[[Category:1868 deaths]]\n[[Category:British male writers]]\n[[Category:Indian Civil Service (British India) officers]]\n\n{{UK-writer-stub}}\n", "